cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

The paper proposes a novel architecture for convolutional networks that increases their representational power while reducing computational complexity. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a gating network to determine the selection and scaling of channels for each input suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed architecture on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
